<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
      i18n:domain="launchpad">

<body>

<metal:leftportlets fill-slot="portlets_one">
  <div class="portlet">
    <h4>About this page:</h4>
    <div class="portletBody portletContent">

      <img src="/++resource++info_icon.gif" />
      This page allows you to modify the link between <span
      tal:replace="context/title">apache in ubuntu hoary</span> and an
      upstream branch. Once we have accurate information about that link, we
      can share bugs, translations, and patches very easily between the
      distro maintainers and the upstream product maintainers.

    </div>
  </div>
</metal:leftportlets>

<metal:rightportlets fill-slot="portlets_two">
  <div tal:replace="structure context/@@+portlet-hctstatus" />
</metal:rightportlets>


<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <h1>Package Upstream Link</h1>

  <p class="documentDescription">Use this page to link
  <span tal:replace="context/displayname">ubuntu hoary evolution</span>
  to its "upstream".</p>

  <p class="portalMessage" tal:condition="not: context/productseries">
    Unable to determine the upstream product series for this package. Please
    add packaging information below!
  </p>

  <p class="portalMessage" tal:condition="view/status_message"
     tal:content="view/status_message">
     Status Message Here
  </p>

  <p>Once the link has been made, it is possible to share
  translations, patches and bugs much more efficiently between the
  distribution maintainers, and upstream maintainers.</p>

  <form tal:attributes="action request/getURL" method="POST">

    <div class="field">

      <label tal:content="view/productseries_widget/label">The Label</label>

      <span
        tal:condition="view/productseries_widget/required"
        class="fieldRequired"
        title="Required">(Required)</span>


      <div tal:content="structure view/productseries_widget">
        <input type="text" style="width:100%"/>
      </div>

      <p class="formHelp"
         tal:condition="view/productseries_widget/hint"
         tal:content="view/productseries_widget/hint">Some Help Text
      </p>

      <div class="portalMessage"
           tal:define="error view/productseries_widget/error"
           tal:condition="error"
           tal:content="structure error">An Error Message</div>

    </div>

    <div class="actions">
      <input
        type="submit"
        name="packaging"
        value="Change"
        i18n:attributes="value submit-button"
        />
    </div>

  </form>

</div>
</body>
</html>
